content: First of all, I am glad to announce that 2 days ago, Renjuclass became 6 years old.
as an old tradition, in the birthday lesson, you will get 2cp each instead of 1.
of course, if you pass the checks.
Lets start with a check then.
Last week, we analysed a TWC game between Sushkov and me.
dongfujia, Erica, attila89, Samsone, manayo, SugarPuffs, Yue, soujun, Laney, smiling, Shangjin, benben, skywalker, Ikon, Renju_liu_t, jinzhiyuye, MIMI, denise, whte, yuelee00.
Today, we will study the two important games from TWC finals - Soosyrv - Artemiev, and Taimla - Chingin.
Both games were won by Russian players.
Ants and Tunnet had made a brief analysis before the beginning of the match,
and they decided that it is safe to play 11-h10.
Tunnet was still thinking, which 11th move to use.
And he was looking at next table, how Ants was doing there.
Because move 14 was not part of Tunnet's and Ants' plan,
so Tunnet did not play 11th move,
until he would see the outcome of this variant on Ants' table.
After long thinking, Ants played j10.
And because Tunnet had already spent over 1 hour on waiting and thinking,
he felt pressure about decision making.
He tried to evaluate, whether Russians might have some trap there,
concluded shortly that its safe for black,
and then repeated the same 11th move....
Then, instantly, having seen Tunnet's 11th move on next table, Artemiev revealed the plan that they had prepared together with Chingin before the match.
Somehow, this move had been missed in previous analyses,
and it ended with black advantage.
Now, it was a difficult moment for our team.
g7 is the only move here
Then, both Artemiev and Chingin played their moves fast.
After that, the referee paused the game Soosyrv-Artemiev,
and moved the game to separate room.
is it forbidden to play 2 same games near to each other?
If its a theory path, its ok to have same games,
tunnet should not have a look at the next table
but if its already out of theory, and some moves may help other player,
because maybe he can win as the same
then referee has a right to separate games.
but if one estonian would be white here?:P
because they happened in many games in the past.
Chingin was the one who had made home analysis,
and he had briefly showed Artemiev the variants before the game.
So it was expected that Chingin knows all the wins there (if there is win at all),
and Artemiev could take advantage of it
However, maybe it was not even necessary, because Tunnet and Ants went different ways from this point.
He had remembered wrongly about Chingin's explanation,
and thought that next white move should be at e9
but if so, Ants could win the game.
In the last moment, Artemiev trusted his eyes more than his memory,
so he checked carefully, and decided to follow his eyes
25 gives white the chance to attack
and it became clear than white wins.
do you see white vcf now?
now comes the great white move.
The threat point is i12 again, 4x4
Now after this 26, the situation was hopeless .
White has a vcf threat again, do you see it?
Tactically, it was very unlucky for us.
but it turned out to be unsafe variant.
Ants and I were in Kullo center again, in our renju club,  and discussing about games.
And I asked about this 25th move.
this is a strong defense move
In most variants of this style,
usually i12 is a strongest defense.
Today, we can analyse it together.
Who wants to be white here?
Many of you will have the chance to try.
After all, 2 cps have to be well earned
i try most natural move first
i try one active move first
i hope everybody will try today at least one time
you dont have to see the win before you say "me"
we become stronger by trying and failing
thank you very much! It was also a good idea for an attack. Who will be next?
if you all try at least once, then you can end the lesson with proud feeling,
having made an effort in solution
ok i will choose myself then
hmmm,poor skill man first go,then let me first:)
i am not sure of it yet
very interesting variant so far. the result of this 25th move decides the fate of 11th move.
while thinking, lets have a check
thanks Ikon, very good attack, very good!
